<inglise> REGULATION (EEC) No 2822/71 OF THE COUNCIL of 20 December 1971 supplementing the provisions of Regulation No 17 implementing Articles 85 and 86 of the Treaty </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 2822/71, millega t&auml;iendatakse asutamislepingu artiklite 85 ja 86 rakendusm&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 s&auml;tteid 20. detsember 1971 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 87 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 87, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 (2) of Regulation No 17 1 exempts a number of agreements, decisions and concerted practices from the requirement of notification under Article 4 (1); </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 artikli 4 l&otilde;ige 2 teeb hulgale kokkulepetele, otsustele ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusele erandi artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud teatamisn&otilde;udest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the creation of a common market requires that undertakings be adapted to the conditions of the enlarged market and whereas co-operation between undertakings can be a suitable means of achieving this; whereas it is in particular advisable to encourage co-operation in the field of research and development and the conclusion of specialisation agreements which do not affect competition; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;histuru rajamine n&otilde;uab, et ettev&otilde;tjad kohaneksid laienenud turu tingimustega, ja ettev&otilde;tjatevaheline koost&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;ib olla sobiv vahend selle saavutamiseks; eriti soovitatav on ergutada koost&ouml;&ouml;d uurimis- ja arendusvaldkonnas ning spetsialiseerumiskokkulepete s&otilde;lmimist, mis ei m&otilde;juta konkurentsi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas such co-operation would be facilitated if notification of the agreements, decisions and concerted practices in question were no longer required; </inglise>
<eesti> selline koost&ouml;&ouml; oleks h&otilde;lpsam, kui enam ei n&otilde;utaks teatamist k&otilde;nealustest kokkulepetest, otsustest ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevusest; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in introducing exemption from notification, account must be taken on the one hand of the desire on the part of undertakings that co-operation between them be made easier and on the other of the need for effective supervision; </inglise>
<eesti> teatamisest erandi kehtestamisel tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta &uuml;helt poolt ettev&otilde;tjate soovi, et nende koost&ouml;&ouml; muutuks lihtsamaks, ja teiselt poolt t&otilde;husa j&auml;relevalve vajadust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas agreements, decisions and concerted practices relating only to joint research and development, in so far as they restrict competition, do not as a rule present such dangers as to make notification necessary; </inglise>
<eesti> kokkulepped, otsused ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus, mis k&auml;sitlevad ainult &uuml;hist uurimis- ja arendustegevust, niiv&otilde;rd kui need piiravad konkurentsi, ei kujuta endast sellist ohtu, mis teeks teatamise vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas specialisation agreements may make for improvement in the production and distribution of products; whereas generally there is no reason to fear that competition will be affected provided the participating undertakings do not exceed a certain size and their share of the market in the specialised products does not exceed a given limit; whereas as a general rule agreements of this kind may, pursuant to Article 85 (3) of the Treaty, be exempted from the prohibition imposed by Article 85 (1) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> spetsialiseerumiskokkulepete tulemusel v&otilde;ivad tootmine ja toodete vahendamine pareneda; &uuml;ldiselt pole p&otilde;hjust karta konkurentsi m&otilde;jutamist juhul, kui ettev&otilde;tjate suurus ja nende spetsialiseeritud toodete turuosa p&uuml;sib teatavates konkreetsetes piirides; reeglina v&otilde;ib sedalaadi kokkulepetele vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 85 l&otilde;ikele 3 teha erandi selle artikli 85 l&otilde;ikes 1 kehtestatud keelust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, therefore, Article 4 (2) of Regulation No 17 should be supplemented and agreements, decisions and concerted practices for joint research and development, in so far as they restrict competition, and certain specialisation agreements, should be exempted from compulsory notification; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu tuleks m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 17 artikli 4 l&otilde;iget 2 t&auml;iendada ja vabastada kohustuslikust teatamisest kokkulepped, otsused ja koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus &uuml;hise uurimis- ja arendustegevuse alal ning teatavad spetsialiseerumiskokkulepped, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
